    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i think i might be able to check the capacitor myself if i'm careful. how do i actually tell if the capacitor is the problem vs something else? like is there a specific sign or something i'd see?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A failing capacitor often causes the motor to hum but not start because it can't provide the necessary initial surge of power. You can sometimes tell if it's bad by checking the capacitor's microfarad (µF) rating against the label; if the actual reading is significantly off, it's likely faulty. However, other issues like a seized motor or inadequate voltage could present the same symptom. If you are not comfortable using a multimeter to test capacitance, it is safer to have a professional diagnose it.",
      "source": "target",
